# Columns (space-separated):
#   HOST_KEY  MSP_ID  CRYPTO_PEER_DIR  GATEWAY_PEER  HOST_PEER_PORT  API_PORT  WEB_PORT
#
# HOST_KEY          — service suffix (api-<KEY>, web-<KEY>); unique per row; letters/digits/dots/hyphens
# MSP_ID            — also used to build default chaincode endorsement OR(...,.peer) on deploy
# CRYPTO_PEER_DIR   — directory under fabric-samples/.../peerOrganizations/ (e.g. org1.example.com)
# GATEWAY_PEER      — peer DNS name Fabric expects (e.g. peer0.org1.example.com)
# HOST_PEER_PORT    — gRPC mapped to localhost from test-network (7051 / 9051 / 11051 for sample orgs)
org1 Org1MSP org1.example.com peer0.org1.example.com 7051 8081 8091
org2 Org2MSP org2.example.com peer0.org2.example.com 9051 8082 8092
org3 Org3MSP org3.example.com peer0.org3.example.com 11051 8083 8093